                <fr:title text="Contractible type">Contractible type</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001H.agda" type="external">erct-001H.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>contractible with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex></fr:strong></fr:em> when every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> is equipped with an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _x\colon  a = x]]></fr:tex>. We say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em><fr:strong>contractible</fr:strong></fr:em> when it comes equipped with some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is contractible with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>. We sometimes refer to a contractible type as a <fr:em><fr:strong>singleton</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>8295</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-001I</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Proposition">Proposition</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001I.agda" type="external">erct-001I.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is said to be a <fr:em><fr:strong>proposition</fr:strong></fr:em> when every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex>, the type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible with centre</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex>, i.e. all elements of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> are identified.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>8296</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-001J</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-001J.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Sets">Sets</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001J.agda" type="external">erct-001J.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is called a <fr:em><fr:strong>set</fr:strong></fr:em> when for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:p>The notions of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositional</fr:link> types generate an infinite hierarchy of <fr:em>truncation levels</fr:em> expressing the point after which higher identifications become trivial.</fr:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>8297</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-001F</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-001F.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Indexing of truncation levels">Indexing of truncation levels</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Convention</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001F.agda" type="external">erct-001F.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>truncation level</fr:strong></fr:em> is an integer <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \geq  -2]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>8298</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-001G</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="n-truncated type"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> type</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001G.agda" type="external">erct-001G.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>Given a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001F.xml" title="Indexing of truncation levels" addr="//erct/erct-001F" type="local">truncation level</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, we define what it means for a type to be <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> by induction:</fr:p>
                <fr:ul><fr:li>a type is <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-2]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> when it is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>a type is <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> when it is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, a type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> when for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex> is <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span>.</fr:li></fr:ul>
                <fr:p>So, in particular, a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex>-truncated type is precisely a <fr:em>set</fr:em>. We shall often refer to <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> types as <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-types</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>12</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>20</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:anchor>8299</fr:anchor>
                <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-001T</fr:addr>
                <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-001T.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="n-truncated map"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> map</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001T.agda" type="external">erct-001T.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is called <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> when all of its <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="//erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fibers</fr:link> are <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml" title="n-truncated type" addr="//erct/erct-001G" type="local"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> types</fr:link>. By analogy, we shall also refer to maps as <fr:em><fr:strong>contractible</fr:strong></fr:em> when their fibers are; we shall refer to maps as <fr:em><fr:strong>propositional</fr:strong></fr:em> when their fibers are <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositions</fr:link>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false" hidden-when-empty="true">
