      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>20</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>17562</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="machine">//erct/unstable/442</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>foreign-erct-unstable-442.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Being contractible is a proposition › "><fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001N.xml" title="Being contractible is a proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001N" type="local">Being <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Suppose we have two centres of contraction <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a,a':A]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _\bullet \colon  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}a = x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi '_\bullet \colon \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}a'=x]]></fr:tex> as witnesses of contraction. To identify 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen a,\chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
 with 
 <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathopen {}\left \lparen a',\chi '_\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}]]></fr:tex>
, we employ the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0035.xml" title="Covariant sum of a left-cloven family of path objects" addr="//erct/erct-0035" type="local">covariant sum</fr:link> of each of the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001C.xml" title="Dependent product of path objects" addr="//erct/erct-001C" type="local">pointwise path object</fr:link> structures on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}-=x]]></fr:tex> over the <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0013.xml" title="The intrinsic path object on a type" addr="//erct/erct-0013" type="local">intrinsic path object</fr:link> structure on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, constructing an identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\colon  a = a']]></fr:tex> followed by a homotopy <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H \colon  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_*^{\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}-=x} \chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}
 \sim  \chi '_\bullet ]]></fr:tex>. Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z\colon  A]]></fr:tex>, we compute:</fr:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \begin {aligned}
      
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_*^{\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}-=x} \chi _\bullet \right \rparen \mathclose {}
 z
      &=
      
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _{a'}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_*^{-=z} \chi _z
      \\
      &=
      \chi _{a'}^{-1} \cdot  \chi _z
      \\
      &= \chi '_z
    \end {aligned}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <fr:p>The first and second steps follow from general computation lemmas for transport, and the last step follows from the fact that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001J.xml" title="Sets" addr="//erct/erct-001J" type="local">set</fr:link>, which we may deduce from <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001K.xml" title="Contractible types are propositions" addr="//erct/erct-001K" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001K" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001L.xml" title="Propositions are sets" addr="//erct/erct-001L" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001L" /></fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
